sentences: Georgios "George" Kollias (born August 30, 1977) is a Greek heavy metal drummer and music teacher best known for his work with American technical death metal band Nile.
Around 1999, he started drum lessons with Greek drummer Yannis Stavropoulos, who was a big influence on Kollias.
He also used to be in the Greek melodic death metal band Nightfall, but left the band in 2005 to join Nile.
Kollias made an instructional drumming DVD called Intense Metal Drumming that was released in July 2008.
